This paper deals with the measurement and analysis of censorship on the Internet, which falls under the category of network security and privacy (cs.NI) and cybercrime (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of network tomography, which is a technique used in cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper deals with the repurposing of network management tools and protocols for censorship, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
